@context: E-commerce purchase flow on SauceDemo
@title: swag-labs-checkout
@var: {username} = standard_user
@var: {password} = secret_sauce

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FEATURES DEMONSTRATED:
#
#   @var:               — Static variables declared at the top of the file.
#                         Use them for credentials and test data instead of
#                         hardcoding values inside action steps.
#
#   Auto-Nav annotations (# 📍 Auto-Nav: ...)
#                       — When "auto_annotate": true in
#                         manul_engine_configuration.json, the engine
#                         automatically inserts these comments into .hunt
#                         files whenever the page URL changes. Page names
#                         come from pages.json; unmapped pages show the URL.
#                         These comments are informational — the engine
#                         does not execute them.
#
#   NEAR 'Anchor'       — Contextual qualifier. Biases element resolution
#                         by Euclidean distance to a resolved anchor.
#                         Used here: Click 'Add to cart' button NEAR 'Sauce
#                         Labs Bolt T-Shirt' — the engine first resolves
#                         the jacket text, then picks the closest matching
#                         button.
#
#   VERIFY ... is present
#                       — Assertion after each significant navigation.
#                         Best practice: always verify the expected page
#                         state before continuing.
#
#   Full E2E flow       — Login → browse → add to cart → checkout → verify.
#                         This is the classic pattern for E-commerce tests.
#
#   Commented hook docs — This file also shows how to document lifecycle
#                         hooks without making the shared demo depend on
#                         local helper modules.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Example lifecycle block for a real project (kept commented so this demo
# remains self-contained):
# @script: {auth} = scripts.auth_helpers
# [SETUP]
#     PRINT "Preparing SauceDemo user {username}"
#     CALL PYTHON {auth}.ensure_user with args: "{username}" "{password}"
# [END SETUP]
#
# STEP X: Backend-assisted step example
#     CALL PYTHON {auth}.fetch_cart_seed with args: "{username}" into {cart_seed}
#     VERIFY that '{cart_seed}' is present
#
# [TEARDOWN]
#     PRINT "Cleaning SauceDemo user {username}"
#     CALL PYTHON {auth}.cleanup_user with args: "{username}"
# [END TEARDOWN]

STEP 1: Login
    # 📍 Auto-Nav: https://www.saucedemo.com/
    NAVIGATE to https://www.saucedemo.com/
    FILL 'Username' field with '{username}'
    FILL 'Password' field with '{password}'
    CLICK 'Login' button

STEP 2: Add item to cart
    # 📍 Auto-Nav: Products Catalog
    VERIFY that 'Products' is present
    # NEAR qualifier: resolves the 'Sauce Labs Bolt T-Shirt' text first,
    # then prefers the matching 'Add to cart' button in the same product card,
    # using both visual distance and DOM container affinity.
    CLICK 'Add to cart' button NEAR 'Sauce Labs Bolt T-Shirt'

STEP 3: Review cart
    # 📍 Auto-Nav: Shopping Cart
    CLICK the 'Shopping cart' link
    VERIFY that 'Sauce Labs Bolt T-Shirt' is present
    CLICK 'Checkout' button

STEP 4: Fill shipping info
    # 📍 Auto-Nav: Checkout: Your Info
    FILL 'First Name' field with 'FirstName'
    FILL 'Last Name' field with 'LastName'
    FILL 'Zip/Postal Code' field with '49000'
    CLICK 'Continue' button

STEP 5: Complete order
    # 📍 Auto-Nav: Checkout: Overview
    CLICK 'Finish' button
    # 📍 Auto-Nav: Checkout: Complete
    VERIFY that 'Thank you for your order!' is present
DONE.
